    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 88.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have a confidential
                            communication, under date of October 29, from the governor of Colorado,
                            respecting the postponement of the criminal proceedings against the
                            Walsenburg Italian lynchers, the substance of which I shall be glad to
                            make known to you at our next interview.</p>
                <p>The governor expresses the strongest desire that the guilty parties may
                            be punished and his conviction that the postponement is a necessary
                            means to that end.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
